      <div class="day-hero-content">
       <div class="day-number">
        Day 1
       </div>
       <h2 class="day-theme">Grateful for God's Provision</h2>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="day-body">
      <div class="scripture-box">
       <p class="scripture-text">"O give thanks unto the LORD; for he is good: for his mercy endureth for ever."</p>
       <p class="scripture-ref">‚Äî Psalm 107:1, King James Version (KJV)</p><a href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Psalm+107:1&amp;version=KJV" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="bible-link">Read Full Chapter ‚Üí</a>
      </div>
      <div class="devotional-text">
       <p>As we begin this seven-day journey of thanksgiving, we start with the foundation of all gratitude: God's faithful provision. From the rising of the sun to its setting, the Lord provides for His children with unwavering love and care.</p>
       <p>Consider the harvest‚Äîhow God brings forth fruit from the earth, sustaining us with daily bread. Yet His provision extends far beyond physical needs. He provides wisdom when we lack understanding, peace in times of trouble, and strength when we are weary.</p>
       <p>Today, let us open our eyes to see the countless ways God has provided for us. From the breath in our lungs to the relationships that enrich our lives, every good gift comes from above. As we cultivate a heart of thanksgiving, we recognize that His mercy truly endures forever.</p>
      </div>
      <section class="journal-section">
       <h3 class="journal-title">Journal &amp; Reflect</h3>
