       <div class="day-number">
        Day 2
       </div>
       <h2 class="day-theme">Grateful for Relationships</h2>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="day-body">
      <div class="scripture-box">
       <p class="scripture-text">"A friend loveth at all times, and a brother is born for adversity."</p>
       <p class="scripture-ref">‚Äî Proverbs 17:17, King James Version (KJV)</p><a href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Proverbs+17:17&amp;version=KJV" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="bible-link">Read Full Chapter ‚Üí</a>
      </div>
      <div class="devotional-text">
       <p>God, in His infinite wisdom, created us for community. We were never meant to walk this journey alone. The relationships He has woven into our lives are precious gifts‚Äîeach one a reflection of His love and care for us.</p>
       <p>Think of those who have stood by you in times of trial, who have celebrated your victories, and who have spoken truth into your life. These are not mere coincidences but divine appointments orchestrated by a loving Father who knows our need for companionship.</p>
       <p>Today, let us give thanks for family members who have shaped us, friends who have encouraged us, and even acquaintances who have touched our lives in meaningful ways. May we also be mindful to be the kind of friend and family member that reflects Christ's love to others.</p>
      </div>
      <section class="journal-section">
