     <div class="day-hero">
      <div class="day-hero-content">
       <div class="day-number">
        Day 3
       </div>
       <h2 class="day-theme">Grateful for Trials &amp; Growth</h2>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="day-body">
      <div class="scripture-box">
       <p class="scripture-text">"My brethren, count it all joy when ye fall into divers temptations; Knowing this, that the trying of your faith worketh patience."</p>
       <p class="scripture-ref">‚Äî James 1:2-3, King James Version (KJV)</p><a href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=James+1:2-3&amp;version=KJV" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="bible-link">Read Full Chapter ‚Üí</a>
      </div>
      <div class="devotional-text">
       <p>It may seem counterintuitive to give thanks for trials, yet Scripture calls us to this very practice. Like a tree that grows stronger through storms, our faith deepens through adversity. The challenges we face are not punishments but opportunities for spiritual growth.</p>
       <p>When we look back on difficult seasons, we often see how God was working all things together for our good. The patience we've developed, the character we've built, and the deeper dependence on God we've cultivated‚Äîthese are the fruits of trials endured with faith.</p>
       <p>Today, let us thank God not only for the blessings that bring immediate joy but also for the trials that have shaped us into who we are. In every storm, He is refining us, making us more like Christ, and preparing us for greater purposes.</p>
      </div>
      <section class="journal-section">
       <h3 class="journal-title">Journal &amp; Reflect</h3>
       <div class="journal-prompts">
        <h4>Reflection Prompts:</h4>
        <ul>
         <li>What trial have you faced that ultimately strengthened your faith?</li>
         <li>How have you seen God's faithfulness in difficult times?</li>
         <li>What is God teaching you through your current challenges?</li>
        </ul>
