     <div class="day-hero">
      <div class="day-hero-content">
       <div class="day-number">
        Day 4
       </div>
       <h2 class="day-theme">Grateful for Salvation</h2>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="day-body">
      <div class="scripture-box">
       <p class="scripture-text">"For God so loved the world, that he gave his only begotten Son, that whosoever believeth in him should not perish, but have everlasting life."</p>
       <p class="scripture-ref">‚Äî John 3:16, King James Version (KJV)</p><a href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=John+3:16&amp;version=KJV" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="bible-link">Read Full Chapter ‚Üí</a>
      </div>
      <div class="devotional-text">
       <p>Of all the gifts we could give thanks for, none compares to the gift of salvation through Jesus Christ. Before we knew Him, we were lost in darkness, separated from God by our sin. But in His great mercy, God made a way for us to be reconciled to Him.</p>
       <p>The cross stands as the ultimate expression of God's love‚Äîa love so profound that He sacrificed His only Son for our redemption. Through Christ's death and resurrection, we have been forgiven, justified, and adopted into God's family. We are no longer slaves to sin but children of the Most High God.</p>
       <p>Today, let us pause and reflect on the magnitude of this gift. Salvation is not something we earned or deserved; it is pure grace. May our hearts overflow with thanksgiving for the precious blood of Jesus that has washed us clean and given us eternal hope.</p>
      </div>
      <section class="journal-section">
       <h3 class="journal-title">Journal &amp; Reflect</h3>
       <div class="journal-prompts">
        <h4>Reflection Prompts:</h4>
        <ul>
         <li>What does salvation mean to you personally?</li>
         <li>How has knowing Christ changed your life?</li>
         <li>Who can you share the hope of salvation with today?</li>
        </ul>
