     <div class="day-hero">
      <div class="day-hero-content">
       <div class="day-number">
        Day 5
       </div>
       <h2 class="day-theme">Grateful for Peace</h2>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="day-body">
      <div class="scripture-box">
       <p class="scripture-text">"Peace I leave with you, my peace I give unto you: not as the world giveth, give I unto you. Let not your heart be troubled, neither let it be afraid."</p>
       <p class="scripture-ref">‚Äî John 14:27, King James Version (KJV)</p><a href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=John+14:27&amp;version=KJV" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="bible-link">Read Full Chapter ‚Üí</a>
      </div>
      <div class="devotional-text">
       <p>In a world filled with chaos and uncertainty, the peace of God stands as an anchor for our souls. This is not a peace dependent on circumstances or the absence of problems. Rather, it is a supernatural peace that transcends understanding‚Äîa peace that can calm the storm within even when storms rage without.</p>
       <p>Jesus promised to leave us His peace, a peace unlike anything the world can offer. When we abide in Him, we find rest for our weary souls. His presence brings comfort in sorrow, courage in fear, and hope in despair. This peace guards our hearts and minds, keeping us steady when everything around us shakes.</p>
       <p>Today, let us give thanks for the peace that comes from knowing we are held in the hands of a sovereign God. No matter what we face, we can rest in the assurance that He is in control, He is good, and He will never leave us nor forsake us.</p>
      </div>
      <section class="journal-section">
       <h3 class="journal-title">Journal &amp; Reflect</h3>
       <div class="journal-prompts">
        <h4>Reflection Prompts:</h4>
        <ul>
         <li>When have you experienced God's peace in a difficult situation?</li>
         <li>What anxieties can you surrender to God today?</li>
         <li>How can you cultivate more peace in your daily life?</li>
        </ul>
