    <article id="day6" class="day-content">
     <div class="day-hero">
      <div class="day-hero-content">
       <div class="day-number">
        Day 6
       </div>
       <h2 class="day-theme">Grateful for Purpose</h2>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="day-body">
      <div class="scripture-box">
       <p class="scripture-text">"For we are his workmanship, created in Christ Jesus unto good works, which God hath before ordained that we should walk in them."</p>
       <p class="scripture-ref">‚Äî Ephesians 2:10, King James Version (KJV)</p><a href="https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Ephesians+2:10&amp;version=KJV" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="bible-link">Read Full Chapter ‚Üí</a>
      </div>
      <div class="devotional-text">
       <p>Each of us has been created with divine purpose. Before the foundation of the world, God had a plan for your life‚Äîa unique calling that only you can fulfill. You are not an accident or an afterthought; you are God's masterpiece, crafted with intention and love.</p>
       <p>Our purpose is not found in worldly success or achievements but in fulfilling the good works God has prepared for us. Whether you serve in grand ways or quiet moments, whether your influence reaches many or few, your obedience matters to the Kingdom. Every act of love, every word of encouragement, every prayer offered‚Äîthese are threads in the tapestry God is weaving.</p>
       <p>Today, let us give thanks that our lives have meaning and purpose. We are not wandering aimlessly but walking a path ordained by our Creator. May we embrace our calling with joy, knowing that in serving Him, we find our truest fulfillment.</p>
      </div>
