      <div class="devotional-text">
       <p>As we conclude this seven-day journey, we arrive at perhaps the most sustaining gift of all: hope. Biblical hope is not wishful thinking or blind optimism. It is a confident expectation rooted in the character and promises of God. It is the anchor that holds us steady when waves of doubt and despair threaten to overwhelm us.</p>
       <p>Our hope is built on nothing less than Jesus Christ and His righteousness. Because He lives, we can face tomorrow. Because He conquered death, we have the promise of eternal life. Because He is faithful, we can trust that every promise in His Word will come to pass. This hope does not disappoint, for it is grounded in the unchanging nature of our God.</p>
       <p>Today and every day, let us give thanks for the living hope we have in Christ. No matter what darkness surrounds us, His light shines brighter. No matter what challenges we face, His grace is sufficient. May we abound in hope through the power of the Holy Spirit, and may our lives be a testimony to the hope that is within us.</p>
      </div>
